  </done>
</task>

<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 2: Clean up cosmetic type casts</name>
  <files>src/contexts/EventContext.tsx, src/pages/AutomationTimeline.tsx</files>
  <action>
**EventContext.tsx (INT-07):**
On line 68-70, clean up the double-cast pattern. Currently:
```typescript
fetchFn()
  .then((data: unknown) => {
    const sorted = sortEvents((data as EventData[]) ?? []);
```

Change to a single clean cast:
```typescript
fetchFn()
  .then((data) => {
    // supabase.js returns untyped data; cast at boundary
    const sorted = sortEvents((data ?? []) as EventData[]);
```

Remove the explicit `: unknown` type annotation on the parameter since the cast happens at the usage site.

**AutomationTimeline.tsx (INT-07):**
Remove `(currentEvent as any)` wrapping casts on lines 757, 758, and 771. Since `currentEvent` is typed as `EventData | null` and `EventData` already has `content_config`, `event_date`, and `automation_config` fields:

Line 757 — change:
```typescript
setTemplates(((currentEvent as any).content_config?.whatsapp_templates ?? {}) as WhatsAppTemplates);
```
to:
```typescript
setTemplates(((currentEvent.content_config as Record<string, unknown>)?.whatsapp_templates ?? {}) as WhatsAppTemplates);
```

Line 758 — change:
```typescript
setAutoPilot((currentEvent as any).automation_config?.auto_pilot ?? true);
```
to:
```typescript
setAutoPilot((currentEvent.automation_config as Record<string, unknown> | null)?.auto_pilot ?? true);
```

Line 771 — change:
```typescript
const eventDate = (currentEvent as any)?.event_date ? new Date((currentEvent as any).event_date) : null;
```
to:
```typescript
const eventDate = currentEvent?.event_date ? new Date(currentEvent.event_date) : null;
```

The key improvement: `(currentEvent as any)` bypasses ALL type checking (dangerous). The fixed versions keep type checking on `currentEvent` (EventData) and only cast the specific nested properties where the Record<string, unknown> type is too broad. Line 771 needs no cast at all since `event_date` is already typed as `string | null` on EventData.

Verify with TypeScript LSP that no new type errors are introduced. If `content_config` indexing causes issues, use bracket notation: `(currentEvent.content_config ?? {})['whatsapp_templates']`.
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | tail -20 && npm run test 2>&1 | tail -20</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>
- EventContext.tsx has a single clean cast `(data ?? []) as EventData[]` instead of double cast
- AutomationTimeline.tsx has zero `(currentEvent as any)` patterns
- AutomationTimeline.tsx accesses content_config, automation_config, event_date through typed EventData properties
- TypeScript compiles without errors
- All existing tests pass
  </done>
</task>

